headline: 6 Stocks to Sell in a Hot Market
summary: All of the major U.S. stock indexes are up this year, with the  rising almost 16% and hitting several new highs this year.  Enthusiasm among investors abounds—for companies benefiting from artificial intelligence, the related data-center construction across the globe, the push for manufacturing onshoring in the U.S., a consumer that won’t stop spending money, and lower interest rates.  Another risk is that Big Tech could cut back on its data center investments, which would reduce expected sales for the many companies that build the properties.

headline: 3 Reasons We’re Fans of DoorDash (DASH)
summary: Over the past six months, DoorDash has been a great trade, beating the S&P 500 by 13.3%. Its stock price has climbed to $254.99, representing a healthy 36.2% increase. This was partly due to its solid quarterly results, and the performance may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
